      "writtenOn": "2017-03-30T14:27:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Seems like it\u0027d be a lie.  When I see a set of const methods, I usually assume they\u0027re all safe to call concurrently with each other.  I don\u0027t see any way to make this particular use case thread safe.  We can\u0027t even just shove a mutex in there... we don\u0027t know when the caller is done with the return value.\n\nIf you want things to be const, I think we\u0027ve got to go back to passing the SkTLazy in, or dumping it altogether and always copy.",
